citations:
    citation-got-s07e07:
        source: source-got-hbo
        properties:
            locator: "S07E07 — The Dragon and the Wolf"
            text_from_source: "Bran Stark: 'He's never been a bastard. He's the heir to the Iron Throne.' Sam Tarly: 'He needs to know. We need to tell him.' Intercut with a scene of Rhaegar and Lyanna's secret wedding, and a voiceover revealing: 'His real name is Aegon Targaryen.' Rhaegar's marriage to Elia Martell had been annulled."
            accessed: "2026-03-10"
        notes: "Season 7 finale. Reveals Rhaegar and Lyanna were married, making Jon a trueborn Targaryen (not a bastard), and his true name is Aegon Targaryen. This is show canon only — the books have not yet revealed whether a marriage took place. Note: the annulment of Rhaegar's marriage to Elia is a show-only invention with no book precedent."
